<p>Libyan authorities have opened an investigation into the killing of Saif al-Islam Gaddafi, a son of Libya’s late ruler Muammar Gaddafi. The killing has quickly become a political flashpoint. For some pro-Gaddafi supporters, the victim was a potent symbol — and his death has stirred old loyalties and new tensions.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/y43XX3WQvokki5UHDQzxs-uhoxmheCb7LxIvcBqnLBbiywlC6cne5QAs61VV0Ph6KjwvcRIhliu02C79_Z3qoY3etF7IbvhTQanccXFlbMQM_dL67x-43gkSIohYK9uixU_jODRg9vCBZLas0NhdU5YfdTQZCvG7Dxg6A1zC5qzq10xxeVWcQs45yKqKFIq9ClOwoFX8smCMk8Ao' alt='File photo related to reporting on the investigation into Saif al-Islam Gaddafi’s killing.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Timing: The Guardian said Saif al-Islam Gaddafi was shot dead on Tuesday.</li><li>NDTV framing: NDTV described him as someone once seen by some as his father’s likely heir.</li><li>Political resonance: The Guardian wrote that he tapped into nostalgia for an era some remember as more secure, keeping loyalist sentiment politically relevant.</li><li>Who he was (as described by Al Jazeera): Al Jazeera called Saif al-Islam Gaddafi his father’s “number 2,” highlighting his standing in the former regime’s inner circle.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Libyan prosecutors: The prosecutor’s office said investigators want to “speak to witnesses and anyone who may be able to shed light on the incident,” as they work to determine responsibility for the shooting. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/libya-probes-killing-of-late-ruler-gaddafis-son/article70592811.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>The Guardian analysis: The Guardian argued that Saif al-Islam had come to be seen as a threat to Libya’s governing elite, with loyalist networks still able to mobilize support. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/04/murdered-son-of-muammar-gaddafi-was-perceived-as-a-threat-to-libyas-elite'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>NDTV reporting: NDTV focused on who might be behind the killing and why it happened now, underscoring the case’s political and security stakes. (<a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/who-is-behind-the-killing-of-late-ruler-gaddafis-son-and-why-now-10947304#publisher=newsstand'>NDTV</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/libya-probes-killing-of-late-ruler-gaddafis-son/article70592811.ece'>Libya probes killing of late ruler Gaddafi&#x27;s son</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/who-is-behind-the-killing-of-late-ruler-gaddafis-son-and-why-now-10947304#publisher=newsstand'>&quot;Disabled CCTV, Executed Him&quot;: Who Killed Muammar Gaddafi&#x27;s Son And Why?</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/video/newsfeed/2026/2/4/treacherous-assassination-who-was-saif-al-islam-gaddafi'>‘Treacherous assassination’: Who was Saif al-Islam Gaddafi?</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/04/murdered-son-of-muammar-gaddafi-was-perceived-as-a-threat-to-libyas-elite'>Murdered son of Muammar Gaddafi was perceived as a threat to Libya’s elite</a> - theguardian.com</li></ul>